You can&#39;t nest expressions like you are doing -- `*{ ... ${ ... } ... }` is not valid Thymeleaf syntax.  See the Thymeleaf documentation on [appending texts][1].  In most cases, literal substitutions I think are most expressive.

    &lt;img th:src=&quot;|data:image/jpeg;base64,${encodedImage}|&quot; alt=&quot;Profile Picture&quot;&gt;

Or if you prefer regular String concatenation.

    &lt;img th:src=&quot;&#39;data:image/jpeg;base64,&#39;+ ${encodedImage}&quot; alt=&quot;Profile Picture&quot;&gt;
    
    or
    
    &lt;img th:src=&quot;${&#39;data:image/jpeg;base64,&#39;+ encodedImage}&quot; alt=&quot;Profile Picture&quot;&gt;


  [1]: https://www.thymeleaf.org/doc/tutorials/3.1/usingthymeleaf.html#appending-texts

